Detailed Description

cvmx_uahc::_gprtbimap_hs

This register specifies the high-speed USB instance number to which each USB 2.0 port is connected. By default, USB 2.0 ports are evenly distributed among all high-speed USB instances. Software can program this register to specify how USB 2.0 ports are connected to high-speed USB instances. The UAHC only implements one high-speed bus-instance, so this register should always be 0.

This register can be reset by IOI reset or with UCTL()_CTL[UAHC_RST].
